First, we identify the relevant line items:

- Revenue: "Main Business Revenue" and "Total Revenue" (both are the same)
- Cost: "Total Cost" (which includes all costs) 

Next, the difference between revenue and cost (often called gross profit) is provided directly as "Gross Profit."

From the data:
- Total Revenue = 791,992.51
- Total Cost = 504,930.00

Calculating the difference:
Gross Profit = Total Revenue - Total Cost = 791,992.51 - 504,930.00 = 287,062.51

This matches the "Gross Profit" listed.
